JOS – The Chairman of Plateau state Internal Revenue Service (IRS), Dashe Alart, has challenged the management and staff of the board to improve the state internally generated revenue base. He stated this at a two-day retreat organised for the staff of the board held in Jos, the Plateau State capital. According to him, the board was determined to ensure that the internally generated of the state was improved upon. He solicited the support of the people of the state for prompt payment of their taxes as at when due to enable it meet up with the target set for them by the State Government to generate in 2019. Arlart pointed out that with the implementation of the new minimum wage salary payment of N30, 000 due to commence soon in the state, all hands must be on deck to ensure efficient collection of taxes in the state.